A recent moment where I questioned whether something online was real happened when I saw a short video of a woman giving travel tips in a city I know well. At first it looked totally normal — good lighting, casual street noise, and a very natural speaking style. But the longer I watched, the more small things felt off: her mouth movements didn’t perfectly match the audio, the shadows on her face didn’t change as she turned, and a couple of people in the background seemed to walk in oddly repeated patterns.

I paused the video and realized it was likely AI-generated. It wasn’t obvious at first glance, but something about the subtle “smoothness” of the whole scene made me second-guess it. It was one of those moments where you realize how hard it’s becoming to tell what’s real online.
